00:40:50,561 --> 00:40:52,426
You do now.

504
00:40:53,131 --> 00:40:56,589
A major drug trafficker
will arrive from Seattle tomorrow.

505
00:40:56,768 --> 00:41:00,431
You will set up a meet with these men
at the Dead Dog Farm.

506
00:41:00,605 --> 00:41:02,072
l will?

507
00:41:03,307 --> 00:41:06,743
How will l--?
How will l know him?

508
00:41:08,012 --> 00:41:10,071
You're looking at him.

509
00:41:10,248 --> 00:41:12,739
Him? Him...

510
00:41:12,917 --> 00:41:18,014
Will you excuse me?
l've got a nervous bladder.

511
00:41:21,425 --> 00:41:25,156
Why?!
Why?! Why would you...?

512
00:41:30,968 --> 00:41:32,731
You could have...

513
00:41:46,117 --> 00:41:47,812
ls she gonna be okay?

514
00:41:49,921 --> 00:41:52,321
First time he beat her,
l swore revenge.

515
00:41:52,490 --> 00:41:55,323
Something violent and noble.

516
00:41:55,827 --> 00:41:57,852
She begged me not to hurt him,
made me promise,

517
00:41:58,062 --> 00:42:00,428
said it was for both our sakes.

518
00:42:00,865 --> 00:42:04,266
That was four years ago.

519
00:42:05,870 --> 00:42:08,634
One day, l swear, l'll kill him.

520
00:42:09,507 --> 00:42:12,067
No matter what it costs.

521
00:42:37,301 --> 00:42:39,496
Jeez, Mom,
give me a heart attack.

522
00:42:39,670 --> 00:42:41,194
l'm sorry.

523
00:42:41,405 --> 00:42:44,841
What are you doing here
sitting alone in the dark?

524
00:42:46,410 --> 00:42:50,403
Nothing. Just sitting here.

525
00:42:50,615 --> 00:42:54,483
Well, read a book or something,
will you? lt's creepy.

526
00:43:02,126 --> 00:43:04,390
lt's Dad, right?

527
00:43:04,562 --> 00:43:06,621
He'll be back, you know he will.

528
00:43:06,831 --> 00:43:09,356
This is just some of that
top-secret jazz.

529
00:43:10,268 --> 00:43:12,634
l'm not so sure this time.

530
00:43:19,176 --> 00:43:21,167
l was at the Double R
a couple of weeks ago.

531
00:43:21,712 --> 00:43:26,081
Dad and l, we had this talk

532
00:43:26,250 --> 00:43:29,583
about this dream he had.

533
00:43:29,754 --> 00:43:35,659
lt was a big house in white marble,
lots of lights.

534
00:43:36,727 --> 00:43:40,356
Dad was there, and l was there too,

535
00:43:40,698 --> 00:43:44,759
living a life of deep harmony and joy.

536
00:43:45,436 --> 00:43:49,202
And there was all this stuff
about my future.

537
00:43:49,807 --> 00:43:51,866
Good stuff.

538
00:43:53,945 --> 00:43:57,779
Kind of nice. Mom, it was cool.

539
00:43:58,382 --> 00:44:01,749
Your father
is an extraordinary human being.

540
00:44:03,688 --> 00:44:06,816
My father
is a deeply weird individual.

541
00:44:07,959 --> 00:44:11,087
But he has a lot more going on
under his hat than most people,

542
00:44:11,262 --> 00:44:13,127
that's for sure.

543
00:44:13,297 --> 00:44:16,960
Sometimes when l'm sleeping

544
00:44:17,134 --> 00:44:20,399
he runs his fingers through my hair.

545
00:44:21,572 --> 00:44:24,803
He thinks l don't notice, but l do.

546
00:44:35,453 --> 00:44:37,444
How long have l been gone?

547
00:44:37,989 --> 00:44:41,925
- Two days.
- Strange.

548
00:44:43,027 --> 00:44:44,858
lt seemed much shorter.

549
00:44:46,797 --> 00:44:48,856
Garland!

550
00:44:54,005 --> 00:44:56,997
Bobby, l want you
to put out that cigarette.

551
00:45:03,247 --> 00:45:05,772
Then l'd like you to fix me a cocktail.

552
00:45:05,950 --> 00:45:08,350
A strong one, if you don't mind.

553
00:45:08,519 --> 00:45:10,282
Sure, Dad.

554
00:45:17,361 --> 00:45:19,795
ls everything all right?

555
00:45:20,531 --> 00:45:22,396
No, dear.

556
00:45:22,967 --> 00:45:24,958
Not exactly.



